==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: doormat
<hw>doormat</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a mat placed outside and
exterior door for wiping the shoes before entering.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> welcome mat.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <mark>(figurative)</mark> <def>A person who is habitually
abused, taken advantage of or humiliated; sometimes, one who is
physically weak; <as>as, they used him for a
<ex>doormat</ex></as>.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> weakling.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Doornail</ent>⟦br⟧
